  "text": "# HTTP Filter Chain Extension Architecture in Envoy\n\n## Overview\nThe HTTP filter chain extension mechanism in Envoy is composed of three major components:\n\n1. **Filter Factory Registry**: Handles registration and discovery of HTTP filters\n2. **Filter Context**: Provides metadata about filter configuration during chain creation\n3. **Per-Request Filter Chain Execution**: Manages runtime instantiation and execution of filters for each HTTP stream\n\n## Core Files\n\n### Filter Factory Interfaces (envoy/http/filter_factory.h)\nDefines the core abstractions for HTTP filter chain management:\n- `FilterFactoryCb`: Type alias for a function that accepts `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` and creates filter instances\n- `FilterContext`: Struct containing filter configuration name and extension qualified name\n- `FilterChainManager`: Interface allowing filter factories to apply filter factory callbacks to a manager\n- `FilterChainFactory`: Interface for creating HTTP filter chains when new streams are created\n\n### Filter Interfaces (envoy/http/filter.h)\nDefines filter types and callbacks:\n- `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks`: Interface that filter factories use to add filters to the chain\n- `StreamFilter`: Base interface for HTTP filters\n- `StreamDecoderFilter`: Interface for decoding path filters\n- `StreamEncoderFilter`: Interface for encoding path filters\n\n### Filter Configuration Registry (envoy/server/filter_config.h)\nDefines factory interfaces for filter registration:\n- `HttpFilterConfigFactoryBase`: Base factory class with protocol options support\n- `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory`: Factory interface for downstream HTTP filters; registered in the registry\n- `UpstreamHttpFilterConfigFactory`: Factory interface for upstream HTTP filters to clusters\n- These factories implement `createFilterFactoryFromProto()` to convert protobuf config into `FilterFactoryCb` functions\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n### Filter Manager (source/common/http/filter_manager.h and .cc)\nThe per-request filter chain execution engine:\n- `FilterManager`: Main implementation managing active filters in a stream\n- `FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl`: Nested class implementing `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` interface\n- Manages decoder/encoder filter lists and iteration state\n- Implements `applyFilterFactoryCb()` to execute filter factory callbacks\n- Invokes filters in the correct order (decoder path, then encoder path)\n\n### Filter Chain Helper (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h and .cc)\nStateful filter chain factory support:\n- `FilterChainUtility`: Static utility for creating HTTP filter chains from factory lists\n  - `createFilterChainForFactories()`: Converts filter factory callbacks into active filter instances\n  - `FilterFactoryProvider`: Wraps a filter config provider and disabled status\n  - `FilterFactoriesList`: List of filter factory providers\n- `FilterChainHelper`: Template class for processing filter configurations\n  - `processFilters()`: Converts protobuf filter configs into filter factory callbacks\n  - Handles both static and dynamic (ECDS) filter configurations\n  - Validates filter dependencies and terminal filter constraints\n- Creates singleton `DownstreamFilterConfigProviderManager` and `UpstreamFilterConfigProviderManager`\n\n### Dynamic Filter Configuration (source/common/filter/config_discovery_impl.h and .cc)\nSupport for dynamic filter discovery via ECDS:\n- `HttpDynamicFilterConfigProviderImpl`: Template class implementing dynamic filter config provider\n  - `instantiateFilterFactory()`: Converts protobuf messages to `NamedHttpFilterFactoryCb`\n  - Supports both `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` and `UpstreamHttpFilterConfigFactory`\n- Manages filter configuration subscription and warm-up\n- Handles filter factory resolution from registry by type URL\n\n### Common Factory Base (source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h)\nTemplate base class for filter factory implementations:\n- `CommonFactoryBase`: Generic template implementing both `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` and `UpstreamHttpFilterConfigFactory`\n- Provides `createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped()` for type-safe factory creation\n- Reduces boilerplate for individual filter implementations\n\n## Extension Points\n\nEach HTTP filter implements a factory class (e.g., `source/extensions/filters/http/*/config.h`) that:\n1. Derives from `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` or `UpstreamHttpFilterConfigFactory` (or both)\n2. Implements `createFilterFactoryFromProto()` to parse configuration and return a `FilterFactoryCb`\n3. Registers itself via `REGISTER_FACTORY()` macro in the `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` registry\n4. The returned `FilterFactoryCb` captures configuration state and creates filter instances on invocation\n\n## Execution Flow\n\n1. Configuration Phase:\n   - Filter configurations are loaded via protobuf\n   - `FilterChainHelper::processFilters()` looks up factories in registry\n   - Each factory's `createFilterFactoryFromProto()` creates a `FilterFactoryCb` closure\n   - Closures are stored in a `FilterFactoriesList`\n\n2. Stream Creation Phase:\n   - `FilterChainFactory::createFilterChain()` is invoked per new HTTP stream\n   - Calls `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()` with the factory list\n   - This function iterates through factories and calls `manager.applyFilterFactoryCb()`\n\n3. Filter Instantiation Phase:\n   - `FilterManager::applyFilterFactoryCb()` invokes each `FilterFactoryCb` with a `FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl`\n   - The closure executes its captured configuration and calls callbacks to add filters\n   - Filters are added to appropriate lists (decoder filters, encoder filters)\n\n4. Stream Processing Phase:\n   - `FilterManager` iterates through filters on headers, data, trailers\n   - Respects filter return codes to control chain progression\n   - Handles filter callbacks for headers/data injection and local replies\n\n## Key Design Patterns\n\n- **Factory Pattern**: Filter factories defer actual filter creation until stream time, enabling:\n  - Configuration validation at startup\n  - Lazy filter instantiation only for active streams\n  - Filter instance per-stream isolation\n\n- **Callback-based Composition**: `FilterFactoryCb` closures capture configuration and create filters dynamically\n\n- **Registry Pattern**: `REGISTER_FACTORY()` enables dynamic filter discovery without compile-time dependencies\n\n- **Template Specialization**: `FilterChainHelper` and `HttpDynamicFilterConfigProviderImpl` use templates to handle both downstream and upstream contexts\n\n- **Visitor Pattern**: `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` allows filters to be added without filter manager knowing specific filter types"
}

